  "text": "International Journal of Infectious Diseases j o u r n a l h o m e p a g e : w w w . e l s e v i e r . c o m / l o c a t e / i j i d tuberculosis on the basis of sonographically-guided aspiration for acid-fast bacillus stains, cytological study, and cultures for Mycobacterium. They concluded that sonographic examination and sonographically-guided fine-needle aspiration contributes substantially to the diagnosis of parotid tuberculosis infection. Parotid tuberculosis, though rare, should be included in the list of differential diagnoses for a parotid mass, especially in the presence of rim enhancement and associated necrotic adenopathy. The prognosis is good if treated properly with antitubercular drugs. [CITATION_1] 5 Conflict of interest: No conflict of interest to declare.",
